The following authors have contributed to the ppp-pam project:

  * Thomas Fors <tom@fors.net>

Also cleanups, security fixes and some functions by:
  * Tomasz bla Fortuna <bla@thera.be>

Special thanks to:

  * John Graham-Cumming for creating an implementation of the Perfect Paper
    Passwords algorithm and releasing it to the open source community under
    the BSD license.  John's code was used as the starting point for the code
    you find here, and you may still find some remnants of it intact.
    http://www.jgc.org/blog/2007/10/open-source-implementation-of-steve.html

  * Steve Gibson for developing *and* sharing the Perfect Paper Passwords
    algorithm with loyal listeners of the Security Now podcast.
    https://www.grc.com/ppp.htm

The ppp-pam project utilizes code from the following sources and would like
to acknowledge the following authors:

  * Rijndael Cryptography Algorithm
    http://www.efgh.com/software/rijndael.htm
    Author: Philip J. Erdelsky
    License: Public Domain

  * FIPS 180-2 Hash Algorithms
    http://www.ouah.org/ogay/sha2/
    Author: Olivier Gay
    License: BSD License

  * MPI: Arbitrary Precision Integer Arithmetic Library
    http://www.cs.dartmouth.edu/~sting/mpi/
    Author: Michael J. Fromberger
    License: Public Domain


